The paper deals with a graph problem related to domination, which is a classic topic in computer science. The problem is a generalization of many dominating set type problems, which are usually studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also uses techniques related to branchwidth and treewidth, which are topics studied in the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper deals with planar graphs, which are a special class of graphs studied in the sub-category of cs.GT (Graph Theory). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT, and cs.CG, in this order.
